wxWidgets2.8
------------------------------------------
wxWidgets is a set of libraries that allows C++ applications to compile
and run on several different types of computer, with minimal source code
changes. There is one library per supported GUI (such as Windows, GTK+,
Motif, and Mac). As well as providing a common API (Application
Programming Interface) for GUI functionality, it provides functionality
for accessing some commonly-used operating system facilities, from
copying and deleting files to socket and thread support. wxWidgets is a
'framework' in the sense that it provides a lot of built-in
functionality, which the application can use or replace as required,
thus saving a great deal of coding effort. Basic data structures such as
strings, arrays, linked lists and hash tables are also supported.

